Díaz Jim. &amp; Pérez-Farr.
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[696,781,1141,1166]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[696,781,1141,1166]" pageId="1" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[796,863,1140,1166]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[343,1244,357,1645]" captionTargetId="figure-106@2.[340,1247,353,1648]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Anthurium tacotalpense. A. Cultivated adult plant showing upper surface, lobes and margins of the blades; B. Inflorescence in the male phase with its yellow stamens; C. Portion of spadix in male phase showing the flowers, tepals and pistils with black stigmas (not receptive); D. Infructescence with mature (orange) and immature (green) fruits. Scale bars: A = 10 cm; B = 2 cm; C = 1 mm; D = 2 cm. Photos:A–D: Pedro Díaz Jiménez." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332000" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332000/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="75">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
